Barack Obama receives the Nobel Peace Prize as the fourth US President
American President Barack Obama is coming to Oslo, Norway for 26 hours to receive the Nobel Peace Prize here as the fourth US President in history.
In addition, he receives the diploma and the medal and a check of 1.4 million dollars for his extraordinary efforts to intensify world diplomacy and cooperation among the peoples.
The head of the White House will arrive tomorrow with his wife Michelle in the Northwegian metropolis and will be busy all the time.
First, he pays a visit to the Nobel Institute, where he meets for the first time with the five committee members who elected him in October from 172 people and 33 organisations.
The presidential couple then planned a meeting with King Harald V of Norway and Queen Sonja.
In the afternoon, the visit reaches its climax with the ceremony at which Obama takes over the prestigious prize.
He received the award as the fourth US president, but only as the third to receive the prize directly in office.
The White House has already announced that Obama will talk about the war in Afghanistan when he takes over the price.
The President does not want to avoid this issue because he knows that he will accept the prize as a president who is currently waging war in two countries.
A few days ago, he reinforced the war effort by sending more troops to Afghanistan, which none of his critics forgets to emphasize.
At the ceremony Obama also received the Gol Medal, the Diploma and the cheque for ten million Swedish crowns (about 24 million Czech crowns).
He intends to donate the money for charitable purposes, but he has not yet decided on a concrete charitable work.
The program of events will then include a banquet with the President and his wife, at which, in addition to Norway's King and Queen, the Prime Minister and another 250 invited guests will be present.
Obama was very reserved from the beginning to the price.
For example, he said that he felt that he did not quite deserve the price.
He also repeated several times that the price is not only for him, but for all those who aspire to the same values as him.
Immediately after the announcement, he stated that this was "a request to act" for him.
