The president hesitated for three months, but didn't come up with a better idea and so he cheated on the general wenist for 10,000 soldiers.
From Europe, he has pressed the pledge for another 5,000, even though he originally expected at least 10,000.
His plan to withdraw troops from Afghanistan within 18 months and to complete this process within three years is highly problematic in the whole Obama strategy. The whole Obama doctrine leaves more questions than answers.
Some doubt that the halved increase will have the same effect as the measure in Iraq.
Even in spite of the fratricidal war of recent years, Iraq's society is relatively well structured, its leaders honor the values.
The Afghan situation is characterized by contraindication - nobody can be relied on and no agreements are kept.
Under these conditions, it is difficult to prepare the Afghan security forces who are used to changing their minds every day.
The political institutions, even if formally established correctly, remain only bogus buildings, behind which patriarchal tribal relations will continue to grow.
The balance of interests between the different ethnic groups is unusually complicated, especially because of the ambiguity of the conditions that complicate Pakistan and Iran's influence even further.
The building of a "active state" which is the minimalist goal of the entire operation is also very unrealistic.
Time horizon of Obama’s strategy puzzled by its voluntarism
Over the last eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has only deteriorated further and now it is on the brink of the explosion.
Believe in the fact that the little soldiers who have broken into the war cry about the "early homecoming" create a miracle here, can only a really romantic soul, which cannot be impressed by facts.
From a political point of view, the date for the withdrawal of troops is pure irresponsibility, because the Taliban will accept this as the indirect confession of American defeat.
The last NATO summit showed that the willingness of Europeans to participate in the fighting in Afghanistan is running out.
Europe's politicians cannot and do not want to explain to their voters how the security of Germany or Italy is linked to the war in the Hindu Kush foothills.
Another possible factor that can radically influence the situation is the development of events in Iran.
If the situation continues to deteriorate and the increased sanctions do not affect the Iranians, the United States will face a very serious question as to whether the problem cannot be solved with troops.
This question has to be answered during the period when America is moving to the victory withdrawal from Afghanistan after Obama.
But any solution will also mean a dramatic change in the Afghan situation.
The only consolation for Barack Obama is the fact that three more years remain until the presidential election, and thus there is still enough time for him to resort to another strategy that would turn out to be a total failure.
