From January, children can be vaccinated for free against pneumococci born on 2 August last year and later.
The condition is that they have not yet received a dose of vaccine.
Those who have already started vaccination in the past year or earlier must also pay for further repeated vaccination themselves.
The first dose should be given between the 3rd and 5th month of life of the child.
Last year, a quarter of families had their children vaccinated against pneumococci.
The parents paid 1600 kroner and more for one dose.
Vaccination of the youngest children requires four doses.
