However, they save on the treatment that the children would need without vaccination.
Until now, the state has spent about 500,000 per year on all area vaccinations of the children.
The mandatory vaccination was introduced with the so-called Janota package.
Pneumococci cause middle ear inflammation, but also severe infections including meningitis and blood poisoning.
Pneumococcal infections cause up to 28 children up to 10 years of age to die in hospitals every year.
Outside the Czech Republic, the compulsory vaccination of children against pneumococci was introduced in about 40 countries.
Will the vaccination be mandatory?
At the same time, it is said that this vaccination could be mandatory in the future.
From January this is to be paid by the insurance companies and voluntary.
For example, Rudolf Kalovsky, head of the Nahlas Association of Citizens, mentioned that the mandatory vaccination would be better.
