We have to stop the terrorists down there, she says.
Obama, who inherited two wars from his predecessor George W. Bush, the wars in Iraq and Afghanistan, tried to justify the use of force in Oslo on Thursday; a way to explain his decision nine days ago to send 30,000 additional soldiers to Afghanistan.
Another opponent of Obama, Newt Gingrich, believed that the President had done "very good work" in Oslo.
I thought that the speech was really very good, ex-president of the House of Representatives exclaimed, who particularly acknowledged the reference to "the existence of evil in the world" in Obama's words.
